## Wrap-up protocol

Everything from here to "Anti-patterns" governs the wrap-up half: the `changes/<slug>.md` doc, the two-commit strategy, the per-template substance hints, and the generic-adaptation notes for forks. The wrap-up doc draws its requirements (§3) from the intake bundle you captured above.

### Definition of Done

A piece of work is done when ALL of these are true:

1. The intake protocol above was run at the start of the work — ticket confirmed, AC text transcribed and confirmed by the user.
2. Code/metadata changes deploy cleanly to the working sandbox.
3. Targeted Apex tests pass with the project's required coverage.
4. Apex log retrieved and grepped for hidden `EXCEPTION|ERROR|FATAL` per [`test-deploy-ruleset.mdc`](test-deploy-ruleset.mdc).
5. The two commits exist (see "Two-commit strategy" below): one for code, one for the `changes/` doc.
6. The `changes/<slug>.md` doc is filled in — no stub sections, no `<...>` placeholders left over, and §3 contains the transcribed AC text from intake (NOT a screenshot reference).

