## Naming convention for the doc

`changes/<short-kebab-slug>.md` — short, kebab-case, descriptive of the work itself (not of the ticket number).

| Good | Bad |
|---|---|
| `account-trigger-recursion-fix.md` | `fix1.md` |
| `add-bulk-import-omniscript.md` | `STORY-12345.md` |
| `hfn-creation-async-batch-migration.md` | `refactor.md` |
| `practitioner-creation-flow-issues.md` | `JIRA-fix.md` |

A ticket reference belongs **inside** the doc (in the header block or §3 Requirements), not in the filename. Filenames must read well a year from now without the ticket tracker open.

---

## Required header block (top of every doc)

Every `changes/<slug>.md` starts with this block — same shape across all four templates:

```markdown
**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Sandbox:** `{{ORG_ALIAS}}`
**Lead:** <Name> (<role — e.g. developer, sysadmin, sysadmin + developer>)
**Story / ticket:** [<TRACKER-NNN>](<url>) — <one-line summary>
**Code commit(s):** [`<short-hash>`](#deploy-ids-and-commit-references) (latest; full list in section X)
**Manifest:** [`manifest/<feature>.xml`](../manifest/<feature>.xml) (the deploy manifest used; contents inlined in section X)
**Status:** Resolved / Delivered / In progress / Pending observation on <list>
```

Notes on each line:

- **Sandbox** alias for this repo is **`{{ORG_ALIAS}}`** (confirm via `sf config get target-org` or `sf org list --all`).
- **Story / ticket** comes from the intake protocol (Step A).
- **Code commit(s)** — singular hash for one-shot work; comma-separated list for iterative threads (see "Same thread, same doc" below). `<short-hash>` is the first 8 chars of the code commit SHA captured in step 3 of the two-commit strategy.
- **Manifest** — the `manifest/*.xml` file used for the deploy. This field is REQUIRED whenever the work involved a `sf project deploy start` or `sf project retrieve start` invocation with `--manifest`. Inline the manifest's full XML content in the "Deploy IDs and commit references" section of the doc — reviewers shouldn't have to open a second file to know exactly what got deployed.

