## What good looks like

Three short examples (one per template) showing the kind of substance a section needs.

### Bug-fix example — root cause section

```markdown
### Family 1 — Formula field write (`IsActive -> Status_Active__c`)

**Field metadata** (verified by anonymous Apex `Schema.DescribeFieldResult`):

| Object | Field | IsCreatable | IsUpdatable | IsCalculated |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `Order__c` | `Status_Active__c` | false | false | true (formula) |

The DataRaptor `DR_OrderStatus_1` mapped a top-level `IsActive` input to the
formula field `Status_Active__c`. The formula is `IF(Status__c = 'Active', true, false)` —
Salesforce always derives it; a client-supplied value is never persisted.

Why the prior package version tolerated it: silent strip before DML.
Why the new version rejects it: strip removed; Salesforce raises
`Unable to create/update fields: Status_Active__c`.
```

### Story example — design decisions section

```markdown
### 4.1 — Async vs sync HFN creation for the new bulk import

**Decision:** Run HFN creation in a Queueable chained from the OmniScript, so
the user gets a sub-3-second response and HFN records appear within ~30 seconds.

**Alternatives considered:**

| Option | Pros | Cons | Why rejected |
|---|---|---|---|
| Queueable chain (chosen) | <3s user response | Eventual consistency window | (chosen) |
| Synchronous in OmniScript | Records visible immediately | Blocks user 18-25s on bulk imports | UX unacceptable per AC2 |
| Batch Apex | Handles >50 records cleanly | Slower kickoff (~5min) | Most imports are <20 records; latency unacceptable |
```

### Refactor example — behavioral invariants section

```markdown
| Invariant | How preserved | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| `AccountHandler.afterUpdate` writes AccountHistory for `Status__c` and `OwnerId` | Kept the two `update acc.Status__c` and ownership-transfer paths byte-equivalent | `AccountHandlerTest.testStatusHistory` and `testOwnerHistory`, both pass |
| Trigger fires only in `BeforeInsert`/`BeforeUpdate` contexts | Context router preserved at top of new `AccountHandler.run()` | `AccountHandlerTest.testTriggerContextRouting` |
| FLS check uses `with sharing` | New service class declared `with sharing` (was `with sharing` before) | Code review + grep for `without sharing` returns no hits |
```

